  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_24",
    "text": "Fourth solution: We apply induction on n, the case n = 1 being evident. First we verify the auxiliary inequality",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5582706813583717,
      0.6061046513738152,
      0.9172932260977686,
      0.633720929585487
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_9",
    "text": "and likewise with the roles of a and b reversed. Adding these two inequalities and clearing denominators yields the desired result.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.12781954970176249,
      0.6307043650771427,
      0.49060151260400175,
      0.6716269841159829
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001",
    "order": 20
